21/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Sarajevo Cantonal Interior Ministry (MUP) arrested a suspected war criminal on Friday (19 September) on the Nisicka highlands in the Ilijas municipality. He was identified as Ostoja Sando, but no further details were released.
In other news, MUP said it would undertake all necessary measures to secure the peaceful arrival of the Bosnian Serb Republic Camp Inmates Association at the BiH Court. The court is located at the former Viktor Bubanj barracks and the ex-prisoners of war are to hold a commemorative ceremony there. The BiH Interior Ministry has refused them actual entry into the building. (SRNA, FENA - 19/09/03)
